<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blackwall" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hogna ingens" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Hogna ingens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed from all other Madeiran 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hogna" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Hogna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the aspect of its legs, blackish with white patches (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Photograph of H. ingens. Female specimen in the field. Photograph credit Pedro Cardoso." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646993" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 26" captionStartId="F26" captionText="Figure 26. Plate with photographs of the lateral view of the leg I for easily diagnosable species." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647006" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">26C</figureCitation>
), and additionally by its genitalia. In males, according to literature, by the inclined palea shield (
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J" journalOrPublisher="Beitraege zur Araneologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 619" refId="B76" refString="Wunderlich, J, 1992. Die Spinnen-Fauna der Makaronesischen Inseln: Taxonomie, Oekologie, Biogeographie und Evolution. Beitraege zur Araneologie 1: 1 - 619" title="Die Spinnen-Fauna der Makaronesischen Inseln: Taxonomie, Oekologie, Biogeographie und Evolution." volume="1" year="1992">Wunderlich 1992</bibRefCitation>
: 596, fig. 720f). In females, by short epigynal anterior pockets, with lateral borders divergent and anteriorly swollen median septum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Hogna ingens female (CRBALC 0591): A epigyne, ventral B vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, female genitalia: H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646992" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">12A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
